            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1698917459607-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef mince is lightly browned, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>to the dish with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> honey</strong>,<strong> Chinese rice wine </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 15 min</p><p>After 15 min add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> and cook covered for a further 10 min or until the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened – this is your<strong> oven-baked honey & soy beef</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
